steps.description:
File: src/runs/reap/auto-plan-run.ts, line 212.

The early-exit guard `workspacePlanIds.size <= baselinePlanIds.size` incorrectly skips dispatch when an agent deleted an old plan and created a new one in the same run (net-zero size change). The only sound check is whether workspace contains any plan ID that baseline does not.

Fix: remove the size check from the early-exit, and instead compute the set difference inside the loop or at the top of the function:

```ts
// before
if (
  workspacePlanIds === null ||
  baselinePlanIds === null ||
  workspacePlansBody === null ||
  workspacePlanIds.size <= baselinePlanIds.size
) {
  return { created: false, id: null, planId: null };
}
```

```ts
// after
if (
  workspacePlanIds === null ||
  baselinePlanIds === null ||
  workspacePlansBody === null
) {
  return { created: false, id: null, planId: null };
}
// The loop already skips baseline plans via `if (baselinePlanIds.has(planId)) continue;`
// so no additional early-exit is needed â€” let the loop do the work.
```

Add a unit test case: baseline=[pl-old], workspace=[pl-new] (both size 1), expects autoPlanRunCreated=true.
